President Joe Biden has announced his intent to nominate Lisa Peterson as Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary to the Republic of Burundi. Peterson is a career member of the Senior Foreign Service and currently serves as the Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary in the Department of State's Bureau of Democracy, Human Rights, and Labor. She has previously served as the U.S. Ambassador to the Kingdom of Eswatini and has held various positions in different U.S. embassies around the world. Peterson earned a Bachelor of Arts degree from the University of Rochester.